    "body": "Now it also occurs to me that you might want to two ways to make a Tx:\n1. The Ethereum instance manages the private key: Ask the Ethereum instance to make and the transaction.\n    + edit: or maybe A can ask the ethereum instance to make the transaction, but the Ethereum instance asks B instead.\n2. The application manages a private key: It creates a transaction and sends the signed transaction.\n\nThe bit that signs it basically has the problem 'does the user really want to send this message?' Imo contract/interface-to-contract writers might have to be able to write a little code so they have some control over what the user sees before signing a transaction.\n",
