    "body": "I thought of the same pattern. There should be a JSON RPC Client that implements the public API. Whats more the ethereum browsers (GUI, CLI) could connect this way too. This could allow clients to easily connect to a full mining node (from gadgets, or mobile devices which do not run a full node). There could be admin interface and remote reactor either as capabilities or with their own json-rpc server.\nWhen refactoring the keymanager, I already thought of a remote keystore with encrypted wallet. Although running your own full node in the cloud with private ports with ssl is pretty good privacy, the idea that your private key would never leave your local device while it is connected to a remote ethereum node is tempting and possible.\n",
