    "body": "@zelig i think that is what lightweight clients are for? I would suspect that ethereum entities running on a cloud service to in effect be a single Ethereum instance, at best. It is a risk to decentralization.\n\nLightweight clients is a possible answer to the idea of the JSON RPC of course; \"the proper way to do it is not the JSON RPC, but a lightweight client\". But then i see no harm to JSON RPC if it only connects securely between things owned and _controlled_ by the same person.\n\nHard wallets for instance sound interesting. If you have a lot at stake, private keys .. well i would have different levels of security and ability on different keys, and maybe use multiple computers to boot..\n",
