    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The idea is that Ethereum will run a `master` node and any other node that starts will look if there's a master node present on the computer (or by telling it to connect to something). This will **not** be done through the public API or any other form of JSON overhead. Simple TCP will suffice.\n\nIf said master node is present it will `register` it self as a child node on the master node and any ethereum activity will be passed along to the child nodes.\n",
